@skensell great report.  Question: why is your cell node a different size from the cell containing it?  I don't recall why this change was made, but I know it was because of a situation that required being able to set the containing cell color.

It is possible that this only makes sense to do for opaque colors, to prevent blending or bleed-through of unintended content beneath.  But I agree with you, ideally the ASCellNode is the same size as the parent and it wouldn't matter.

Lastly, it's really expensive to use cornerRadius on a cell, so consider if you can use an ASButtonNode or ASImageNode with [UIImage as_resizableRoundedImageWithCornerRadius:].  It works with semitransparent background colors and also content showing through behind the corners, as long as the background color is flat (single color, even if alpha) and there aren't any views moving through the inside of the corners that need to be clipped.  http://asyncdisplaykit.org/docs/corner-rounding.html . Hope this is helpful, but I know it's not your main issue and we'll try to help out there too :)

