For what it's worth, using ASDK with Pop is essentially the same as using UIKit with Pop ‚Äî in terms of how you structure the animation and layout code.  However, there's a brilliant synergy between the two frameworks, because Pop (and UIKit Dynamics / any physics-simulating animation system) is very very sensitive to stalls on the main thread.  Check out my NSLondon talk for some discussion of this: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=h4QDbgB7RLo

